multicall(bytes[]).details: Apply `DELEGATECALL` with the current contract to each calldata in `data`, and store the `abi.encode` formatted results of each `DELEGATECALL` into `results`. If any of the `DELEGATECALL`s reverts, the entire transaction is reverted, and the error is bubbled up.

documentation.text:
@dev Apply `DELEGATECALL` with the current contract to each calldata in `data`,
 and store the `abi.encode` formatted results of each `DELEGATECALL` into `results`.
 If any of the `DELEGATECALL`s reverts, the entire transaction is reverted,
 and the error is bubbled up.

@notice Contract that enables a single call to call multiple methods on itself.
 @author Modified from Solady (https://github.com/Vectorized/solady/blob/main/src/utils/Multicallable.sol)
